article.headline: Penn 67, Harvard 53
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Mark Zoller scored 17 points and reserve Brennan Votel had a career-high 11, leading Penn to a 67-53 victory over Harvard on Saturday night. Brian Grandieri and Steve Danley each had 10 points for Penn (14-8, 5-1 Ivy League). Ibrahim Jaaber, the Ivy League's career steals leader, raised his career total to 279 with six steals. Jim Gofferdo had 14 points and a career-high seven steals for the Crimson (10-12, 3-5), who lost their 10th straight game to the Quakers. Penn led 32-26 at the half, and 48-37 after a three-point play by Zoller with 8:58 left in the game. Harvard then closed within 50-44 on two free throws by Gofferdo, but the Quakers ran off 10 straight points, six by Kevin Egee, to help seal the win. Penn scored 13 straight points early in the first half to take a 15-7 lead, but Harvard answered with a 14-4 spurt to move out to a 21-19 lead. Penn came right back with a 13-2 run to take a 32-23 lead and never trailed again.
